President Obama has nominated Carole Schwartz Rendon to serve as U.S. Attorney for the Northern District of Ohio. Rendon has been serving as the Acting U.S. Attorney since February 2016 and has an extensive background in public service and law. President Obama praised Rendon's dedication and accomplishments, stating that she is one of the best in her profession. Rendon has previously worked in various law firms and served in the United States Attorney's Office in Massachusetts. She holds a J.D. from Northwestern University Pritzker School of Law and a B.A. from Northwestern University.